“Kronos is the craziest, most challenging dog I've met over the past few years, and the most unique in looks and personality. When I first met him, I didn't think he'd be part of my family, but now I can't imagine my life without him. He is a wise old soul and teacher and one of my nicknames for him is my CoyDog.
I'm convinced he has a little wild blood in him because of the way he acts sometimes and his jackal-ish looks. The coyote is also the notorious Trickster and Kronos is that to a T. I may have "rescued" him by adopting him and giving him a home and a family, but he has given me so much more. He makes me laugh, smile, and remember to lighten up.
He challenges me to live in the moment and keep an open mind. Because of him I've learned very subtle canine communication and he's opened my eyes to the deeper beauty and even more intricacies of the human animal bond and animal language. He is such a goof, very vocal, expressive, and quite a character. He is far from perfect, and we have some things we are still working on, but he has already come such a long way from where he was, and I'm lucky to share my life with and learn from such an amazing pup.”
